summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1345, entitled "An Ordinance granting to the Northern Pacific and Puget Sound Shore Railroad Company, its successors or assigns, the right and authority to locate, construct, lay down and maintain a standard gauge railroad, consisting of one or more tracks, upon and along a strip of land hereinafter described and to operate said railway upon the conditions prescribed in this ordinance", approved April 30, 1890.
